Iavan Pijoos, News24(File, News24) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Johannesburg - The body of a man was found in the boot of a burnt-out vehicle in Naturena, south of Johannesburg, police said on Tuesday. "We received an anonymous call at 03:00 on Monday morning, stating that there was a car burning in the area. We immediately attended to the scene," Captain Mavela Masondo said.Police found a BMW with a corpse in the boot. The man was not burnt beyond recognition.&nbsp;He urged anyone who may have seen what happened to come forward with information.&nbsp;Police are investigating a case of murder. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.